1
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:34,990
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,450 --> 00:01:37,960
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:40,780 --> 00:01:44,250
Dad had this brought to us.

4
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:47,430
He misses us.

5
00:01:47,870 --> 00:01:49,990
Hongmei, Zongbao said

6
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,300
he wouldn't wire the money this time.

7
00:01:52,620 --> 00:01:54,430
He heard I was coming back,

8
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:55,650
so he asked me

9
00:01:55,789 --> 00:01:57,320
to bring it to you directly.

10
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,080
Uncle Wang, my mom is asking

11
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,520
if my dad has many acting jobs in Beijing

12
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,340
and if he's tired from acting.

13
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:19,040
Yes, he has loads of acting jobs.

14
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:21,340
Your dad is quite a busy man.

15
00:02:23,579 --> 00:02:24,110
Xiaobao!

16
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,500
Look at this. Look.

17
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:27,970
Look what your dad bought you—

18
00:02:27,970 --> 00:02:29,430
Beijing local specialties.

19
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:30,680
Look. What is this?

20
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:32,210
Tuckahoe cake.

21
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:34,020
What is this?

22
00:02:34,650 --> 00:02:36,010
Preserved fruit.

23
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:37,380
And what about this?

24
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:40,010
Eight Beijing-style Pastries.

25
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:42,079
Everyone who has been

26
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:43,610
to Beijing would buy these.

27
00:02:43,970 --> 00:02:44,620
Your dad

28
00:02:44,630 --> 00:02:45,360
went from shop to shop

29
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,800
to buy you every famous specialty.

30
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,600
He also told me

31
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:48,680
to keep them

32
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,340
from being crushed on the way.

33
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:52,890
Hongmei.

34
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:56,450
Zongbao is very frugal.

35
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:57,130
Look.

36
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,650
He couldn't bear to throw away
these old clothes,

37
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,400
saying

38
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:03,730
that they should be kept
for working in the fields.

39
00:03:04,910 --> 00:03:06,970
I didn't have much luggage this time,

40
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:09,470
so I brought these things back with me.

41
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,200
It saved postage as well.

42
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,190
Listen,

43
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:14,740
Zongbao asked me

44
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,960
to bring you two to reunite with him
in Beijing

45
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,940
when I go back there in a few days.

46
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,060
I have things to do.

47
00:03:22,579 --> 00:03:23,500
I need to leave now.

48
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,700
I've got things to do.

49
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,360
I'll walk Uncle Wang out.

50
00:03:26,690 --> 00:03:27,800
I'll walk Uncle Wang out, Mom.

51
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,930
No need to see me off!

52
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:30,900
Stop there!

53
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:59,150
Uncle Wang,

54
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,860
what roles does my dad act in Beijing?

55
00:04:01,970 --> 00:04:03,900
Does he still play the guerrillas?

56
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:07,000
Yes, he plays any kind of role.

57
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,180
He acts in whatever pays him most.

58
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,080
During these years
my dad spent in Beijing,

59
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,280
he keeps talking about acting in shows.

60
00:04:14,470 --> 00:04:16,120
But why haven't I seen him

61
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:18,029
in any drama or movie even once?

62
00:04:18,690 --> 00:04:20,750
All my classmates say I'm just lying.

63
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:22,100
Also, Uncle Wang,

64
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,850
just now when my mom asked you

65
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:26,550
if my dad was tired from acting
in Beijing,

66
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:28,860
why did you suddenly freeze up?

67
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:32,070
Kid,

68
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:35,040
there's no job that isn't tiring.

69
00:04:36,370 --> 00:04:37,630
Do you think money in Beijing

70
00:04:37,630 --> 00:04:38,800
grows on trees,

71
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:40,450
that you can reach it with your arms

72
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:41,710
or bend down to pick it?

73
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,130
When you grow up,

74
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,680
you will understand.

75
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:49,190
In the future,

76
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:51,730
you must treat your dad well.

77
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:53,350
I'm leaving now.

78
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:14,390
Mom, Mom.

79
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:54,870
Morning, Ms. Yue.

80
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,160
Lucy, wait a minute.

81
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:06,910
Come here.

82
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,180
Do a spin.

83
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,070
This sweater of yours

84
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:14,330
doesn't seem to be from any brand.

85
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,460
Where did you buy it?

86
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,830
I designed it myself

87
00:06:16,890 --> 00:06:18,420
and had my mom make it for me.

88
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:20,360
You can do design drawings?

89
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:21,430
Oh right.

90
00:06:21,430 --> 00:06:22,540
One of today's design drawings

91
00:06:22,540 --> 00:06:23,470
was done by Lucy.

92
00:06:25,810 --> 00:06:26,470
Take a seat.

93
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:27,000
Okay.

94
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,280
Alright. Let's get started.

95
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,190
Ms. Yue,

96
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,360
these are Team No. 1's

97
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:35,890
designs.

98
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,980
Please take a look.

99
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:41,980
[Designer: Tracy]

100
00:06:49,430 --> 00:06:50,270
Oh right, Toby,

101
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:51,120
later on, make me

102
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:51,870
a drawing

103
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,130
of Lucy's sweater.

104
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:56,450
Got it.

105
00:06:59,130 --> 00:06:59,750
Ms. Yue,

106
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,530
the first two designs are mine.

107
00:07:03,650 --> 00:07:04,990
[Designer: Toby]

108
00:07:05,010 --> 00:07:06,980
[Designer: Toby]

109
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:07,920
Nice designs.

110
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,760
You've made progress.

111
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:10,720
Not bad.

112
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:12,630
You guys

113
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:14,160
should all learn from Toby.

114
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,350
[Designer: Lucy]

115
00:07:22,510 --> 00:07:23,220
[Designer: Lucy]

116
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:25,010
This drawing of Lucy's is confirmed.

117
00:07:25,010 --> 00:07:26,060
Just make the garment

118
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,660
after touching up the lines.

119
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:32,640
Dismissed.

120
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,060
Ms. Yue,

121
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,800
I'd like to ask...

122
00:07:48,330 --> 00:07:48,870
are you sure

123
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:50,180
about using my design?

124
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,570
Didn't you hear me

125
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,950
assigning tasks just now?

126
00:07:52,950 --> 00:07:54,040
I just found it...

127
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:55,860
a bit unbelievable.

128
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:57,850
Is there anything I need to do?

129
00:07:57,850 --> 00:08:00,250
This concludes your design work this time.

130
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:05,070
Now, give me a pen.

131
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,050
[Designer: Yue Ru]

132
00:08:19,810 --> 00:08:20,810
Ms. Yue, this...

133
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:25,680
Silly girl.

134
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:29,120
Five minutes ago,

135
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:31,470
this drawing was worthless.

136
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:32,940
But now,

137
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,799
because of this name,

138
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:36,600
this drawing will produce at least

139
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,659
hundreds of thousands yuan in sales.

140
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:41,280
That's called personal value. Understood?

141
00:08:41,390 --> 00:08:42,650
You made a good design.

142
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,070
Keep up the good work.

143
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,360
Welcome to the real world.

144
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:52,220
Toby!

145
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,000
Meet me in my office.

146
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:55,550
Keep it up.

147
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,280
Wait a minute.

148
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:11,980
How come I feel

149
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,380
you're different today?

150
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:14,850
How am I different?

151
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,510
You used to be passionate

152
00:09:16,510 --> 00:09:17,770
about every audition.

153
00:09:18,270 --> 00:09:18,910
Why do you look like

154
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:20,170
a wilted flower today?

155
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:22,270
You look utterly listless.

156
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,470
This won't do.

157
00:09:25,410 --> 00:09:28,340
Mr. Cui, how many times
have I been through this?

158
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,150
I'll just be there to fill the space.

159
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,610
The second female lead...

160
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,840
Is that something I dare to dream of?

161
00:09:34,870 --> 00:09:36,940
But today... things are different.

162
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,900
How are things different today?

163
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:40,500
Mr. Cui,

164
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:42,620
now I finally get it.

165
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:44,660
In fact, many things

166
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:46,440
have already been decided.

167
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:48,330
Besides, I'm not good enough.

168
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:50,110
I'm not very pretty

169
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,820
or experienced in acting.

170
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:56,290
And I can never cross the boundary
in my heart.

171
00:09:57,980 --> 00:09:58,440
Mr. Cui,

172
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:00,440
please don't be mad
about what I just said.

173
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:02,550
I am actually very grateful to you,

174
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:04,870
for giving me so many opportunities

175
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:05,860
and so much help.

176
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,370
Too bad that I've seized none of them

177
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:09,500
and always let your effort go to waste.

178
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:13,290
Have you... not seized a chance?

179
00:10:14,130 --> 00:10:15,590
What chance have I seized?

180
00:10:20,650 --> 00:10:21,770
We're going to be late.

181
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:23,220
Let's go upstairs now.

182
00:10:23,220 --> 00:10:24,480
Mr. Cui, rest assured.

183
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:27,950
Even if it's just a formality,
I'll still take it seriously.

184
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,890
The issue with these pleats...

185
00:10:36,890 --> 00:10:37,550
Toby!

186
00:10:37,940 --> 00:10:38,360
Come over.

187
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:38,820
Coming.

188
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:41,020
Get it to me by the end of the day.

189
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,100
Toby.

190
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:46,060
What's up?

191
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:46,880
Where is Toby?

192
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:48,560
He just went by.

193
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,850
No, I mean...

194
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:50,980
Oh, that Toby.

195
00:10:50,980 --> 00:10:52,380
Ms. Yu fired him that day.

196
00:10:53,390 --> 00:10:54,330
Just out of blue?

197
00:10:54,870 --> 00:10:55,510
Why?

198
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:56,840
He was practically

199
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,480
a great contributor to the company.

200
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,050
Two mere failed designs

201
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,710
led to his dismissal.

202
00:11:02,010 --> 00:11:03,700
But many of his designs
were approved before.

203
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,840
Are you silly or what?

204
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:07,100
Could the approved designs still be his?

205
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:22,960
Ms. Yue,

206
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:24,770
there's one thing

207
00:11:24,770 --> 00:11:26,370
I'd like to discuss with you.

208
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:27,960
Go ahead.

209
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:30,940
I know

210
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,170
your name contains great value.

211
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:34,620
But I am

212
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:36,680
the original creator of this design.

213
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:38,670
So, I'm wondering if it's possible

214
00:11:38,670 --> 00:11:40,200
to put my name after yours.

215
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,460
Do you think your name

216
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:45,500
can be put side to side

217
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:46,650
with mine?

218
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,670
As far as I know,

219
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:51,010
all designs,

220
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,140
be they big or small, are copyrighted.

221
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:54,980
Given that, in this regard,

222
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:55,710
you and I are

223
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:57,400
entitled to equal rights.

224
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:58,500
Theoretically, yes.

225
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:06,670
[Costume Design]

226
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:01,550
What do you mean?

227
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:06,030
Theoretically, we are equal.

228
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:08,100
But if you continue to let

229
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,560
such idealistic theories

230
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:11,120
guide every aspect

231
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,320
of your work and life,

232
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,060
you'll be in sheer misery.

233
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:16,560
But this is not an argument of theories.

234
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:17,860
I'm just fighting for

235
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:19,190
the rights I deserve.

236
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,470
The rights you deserve...

237
00:12:21,890 --> 00:12:23,090
How do you prove that?

238
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,410
You did the drawing
with the company's resources

239
00:12:25,410 --> 00:12:26,610
during office hours.

240
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:27,860
Your manuscript

241
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:29,390
is saved on a company-owned computer.

242
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:30,770
But the idea and the core design

243
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:31,530
are both mine.

244
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:32,980
-This is my own creation.
-Okay.

245
00:12:32,980 --> 00:12:33,880
Lucy, stop.

246
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:35,530
I'm now taking two minutes

247
00:12:35,530 --> 00:12:36,860
to say these words to you

248
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:37,940
simply because

249
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:38,940
a friend of mine

250
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:40,090
made a call to me,

251
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,270
saying that a friend of his

252
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:42,170
would like to recommend someone

253
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:43,020
to my company.

254
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,390
For me, your personal value

255
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,440
is entirely built on

256
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:48,970
the value
of those two acquaintances of mine,

257
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,450
but not on yourself.

258
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:51,770
You...

259
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,330
amount to nothing.

260
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,050
I do call your name every day.

261
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:56,860
But so what?

262
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,690
Is your name worth even a penny?

263
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:00,540
My company has shareholders.

264
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:03,460
Suppose one day I did a terrible job,

265
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:04,410
the board would

266
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:06,120
strike my name off at 8:00 a.m.,

267
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:06,720
and a new boss

268
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,150
would be here at 10:00 a.m.

269
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:09,700
Even the morning meeting
would happen as usual.

270
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:11,290
This is called "the mechanism of society."

271
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:12,020
Understood?

272
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,220
It was because I realized this

273
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:15,270
in the early years

274
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,360
that I could become who I am today.

275
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,910
Chinese characters have profound depth.

276
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:31,310
There's also a phrase called "social ill."

277
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,640
Ms. Yue, I don't think

278
00:13:32,910 --> 00:13:33,580
you should disguise

279
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:35,440
concessions as personal growth.

280
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:36,760
In my opinion,

281
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,580
real growth means

282
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,370
to use one's own ability

283
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:41,460
to fight for more opportunities

284
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:43,120
to avoid making concessions.

285
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:45,360
Though I'm only doing an ordinary job,

286
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,050
I don't see the necessity

287
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:46,820
of treating myself

288
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:48,750
as a dispensable supporting role.

289
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,730
Every task I complete with care

290
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:52,860
is experience

291
00:13:52,860 --> 00:13:55,520
for the ideal role I aspire to play
in the future.

292
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:03,760
[Costume Design]

293
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,480
Thank you for taking time with me.

294
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:09,820
No need to pay me for the internship.

295
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:11,270
But this design drawing...

296
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,330
will leave with me.

297
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,080
[Employee ID: Lucy]

298
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:31,650
[Bulletin Board]

299
00:14:27,370 --> 00:14:28,010
It's freezing cold.

300
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:29,470
Maybe just don't eat that?

301
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,890
I need this ice pop to help me calm down.

302
00:14:31,890 --> 00:14:33,170
Isn't the air cold enough to calm you down

303
00:14:33,170 --> 00:14:34,230
without an ice pop?

304
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,750
I quit my job.

305
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,120
Y-You quit your job?

306
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,780
Then I need to calm down too.

307
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,580
I did resign, for real.

308
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:52,940
Well,

309
00:14:52,940 --> 00:14:54,290
there must be a reason.

310
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:56,620
Yesterday,

311
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,770
I was really happy at first,

312
00:14:58,870 --> 00:14:59,790
thinking that Ms. Yue

313
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:01,250
finally picked my design.

314
00:15:01,790 --> 00:15:04,380
But before I could savor the moment,

315
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,580
she crossed out

316
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:06,360
my name

317
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,740
and put hers on it,

318
00:15:08,390 --> 00:15:09,130
claiming only that

319
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:10,730
could put value to my design.

320
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:13,010
In the end, she even said I was nothing.

321
00:15:13,010 --> 00:15:14,490
She must be crazy!

322
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:17,750
She's really insane. Just ignore her.

323
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,530
She not only crossed out your name,

324
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:21,630
but also attempted to use your design.

325
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:22,250
Smart move quitting that job.

326
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:25,540
[End-of-term Performance
of Beijing Conservatory of Music]

327
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:24,220
If I were you, I would've quit too.

328
00:15:24,650 --> 00:15:25,720
What an awful person,

329
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,650
for doing such a thing as a teacher.

330
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,700
Gold shines wherever it is.

331
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:30,960
Right?

332
00:15:31,460 --> 00:15:32,460
D-Don't be upset.

333
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,290
To have my creations properly used,

334
00:15:35,290 --> 00:15:36,740
I must become a boss in the future.

335
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,270
You have my support on that!

336
00:15:38,290 --> 00:15:39,010
On top of that,

337
00:15:39,010 --> 00:15:39,810
I also believe

338
00:15:40,290 --> 00:15:41,150
you will have

339
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:42,530
your own costume design company

340
00:15:42,530 --> 00:15:44,330
as long as you set your mind to it.

341
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:45,980
Then if I become a boss one day,

342
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:47,130
you must work as my advisor.

343
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,200
No problem.

344
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:48,690
We...

345
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,360
will absolutely not bully young people.

346
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,030
And we must respect their creativity!

347
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:53,130
We'll give them high salaries.

348
00:15:53,130 --> 00:15:54,130
And treat them to coffee!

349
00:15:54,130 --> 00:15:55,190
Most importantly,

350
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:56,100
we will respect

351
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,700
everyone's fruits of labor.

352
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:06,270
Does it seem to be

353
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,470
too big a dream for us?

354
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:08,790
How is that big?

355
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:09,740
It's our own dream.

356
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,170
We can make whatever dream we want.

357
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:13,030
It might come true one day, right?

358
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,000
Yes, it might.

359
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:17,290
Originally, I thought

360
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,440
I could learn and make money there

361
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,500
at the same time to pay my lesson fees.

362
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,480
Was my quitting an impulsive move?

363
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,680
How was it impulsive?

364
00:16:25,790 --> 00:16:27,390
It was not an impulsive move.

365
00:16:27,530 --> 00:16:29,280
There are so many jobs you can take.

366
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,280
That boss of yours was overbearing.

367
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:34,700
It's okay.

368
00:16:35,390 --> 00:16:37,650
Things will eventually
sort themselves out.

369
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:39,080
In this vast city of Beijing,

370
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,010
there must be a job

371
00:16:40,010 --> 00:16:40,670
that I can do.

372
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,000
Exactly, tons of jobs.

373
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,100
Are you free later?

374
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:49,370
Why?

375
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,500
I'd like to take you to a place.

376
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,730
-Let's go then.
-Go.

377
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,040
Let's go.

378
00:17:00,910 --> 00:17:01,590
Come back!

379
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:04,109
Did you forget what happened
in the cinema last time?

380
00:17:04,109 --> 00:17:04,750
It's all fine.

381
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:06,950
I've scouted this place several times.

382
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,200
Come back, Xu Shengli.

383
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,079
It's too risky.

384
00:17:09,380 --> 00:17:09,880
Hurry.

385
00:17:10,329 --> 00:17:11,460
This really is fine.

386
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,980
Don't you see what time it is now?

387
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:14,460
I'm sure no one will come here.

388
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,109
Besides,

389
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,720
if you are to practice
singing and harmony,

390
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:18,420
you have to do it

391
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:19,670
on a stage like this

392
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,849
-for the best effects, right?
-Keep it down.

393
00:17:21,849 --> 00:17:22,790
And this, look.

394
00:17:23,069 --> 00:17:23,930
The spotlight.

395
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:24,940
Come on, to this spot.

396
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:25,440
Stand here,

397
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,180
right here.

398
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,920
Now with the spotlight on,

399
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,340
you're the only singer

400
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,500
on this entire stage!

401
00:17:33,460 --> 00:17:35,590
There's one more thing. Wait a second.

402
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:37,700
This...

403
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,460
I'll put it here.

404
00:17:41,330 --> 00:17:43,460
Then another one here.

405
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:44,590
What are these?

406
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:46,810
Recorders. I borrowed them.

407
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:49,220
These will provide surround sound.

408
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:52,660
Well, then...

409
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,270
How do you press them both
at the same time?

410
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:58,590
I will just...

411
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,740
Let me show you.

412
00:18:04,220 --> 00:18:05,020
Are you ready?

413
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,090
Three, two, one.

414
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:24,960
Wild geese are flying south.

415
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:28,660
Wild geese are flying south.

416
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:35,680
The cries of wild geese break my heart.

417
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:40,830
Though you're only leaving today,

418
00:18:41,010 --> 00:18:45,590
I am already yearning for your return
in spring.

419
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:52,440
I am already yearning for your return
in spring.

420
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,270
Don't look at me. Look at the audience.

421
00:18:56,270 --> 00:18:57,030
Who's there?

422
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:01,090
Run, now.

423
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:02,180
Come on, this way.

424
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:03,610
Stop running!

425
00:19:03,790 --> 00:19:05,510
Playing "The Phantom of the Opera"
with me, huh?

426
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:06,310
Stop running!

427
00:19:06,810 --> 00:19:07,650
Halt!

428
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:13,040
Guo,

429
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:15,100
pull the rope if you can't take it.

430
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:15,970
The two of us

431
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:16,890
will get you up.

432
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,260
Don't act the hero.

433
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:19,070
I'm fine.

434
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:30,940
It stinks.

435
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:33,140
Will he be fine with this stench around?

436
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,330
Guo. Guo!

437
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,440
Are you okay?

438
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:38,960
Guo!

439
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,160
Not a sound at all.

440
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:40,890
I wonder why.

441
00:19:41,270 --> 00:19:41,830
Guo!

442
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:42,810
What's going on?

443
00:19:42,810 --> 00:19:44,180
We're scared for you!

444
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,070
Guo!

445
00:19:45,610 --> 00:19:47,140
Pull him up. Pull him up now.

446
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:51,590
Get him up.

447
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:52,470
Quick.

448
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,880
Hang in there, Guo!

449
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:54,820
Come on, quick.

450
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,450
Help him out.

451
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:58,940
-Quick.
-Up!

452
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,270
-Up!
-Lean on this.

453
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:03,590
Guo.

454
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:09,640
Are you okay, Guo?

455
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:15,800
Have a rest.

456
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:18,100
Take it easy.

457
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:35,970
Have I fainted or what?

458
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,110
Dad!

459
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:39,330
What?

460
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,500
Dad, get up now.

461
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:44,440
P-Please get up!

462
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,220
Dad!

463
00:20:46,220 --> 00:20:47,980
Why are the two of you here?

464
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:49,720
Hurry, get up, Dad!

465
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:51,160
Dad.

466
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,910
-I smell terrible now.
-Dad!

467
00:20:52,940 --> 00:20:54,080
-I really stink.
-Dad!

468
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:56,070
-H-Hands off me now.
-Get up!

469
00:20:56,180 --> 00:20:57,090
Hands off me.

470
00:21:00,010 --> 00:21:01,500
My clothes stink.

471
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:02,360
I smell bad.

472
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,920
-Dad...
-I smell terrible now.

473
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:06,010
Dad,

474
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:08,600
stop acting!

475
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:09,940
I...

476
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:13,560
Yes, I was just doing...

477
00:21:14,030 --> 00:21:16,690
a scene. A scene.

478
00:21:16,980 --> 00:21:18,640
No, well, I mean...

479
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:20,210
I was doing field research

480
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:21,980
for my next role who is...

481
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:23,570
a sewer cleaner,

482
00:21:23,770 --> 00:21:27,290
just like... Shi Chuanxiang.

483
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:28,590
-Someone like him.
-Dad!

484
00:21:28,590 --> 00:21:30,830
Dad, stop lying to me.

485
00:21:30,850 --> 00:21:31,650
How am I lying?

486
00:21:32,010 --> 00:21:34,330
Xiaobao, let me wash up first.

487
00:21:34,790 --> 00:21:37,050
Then I'll take you out for mutton hot pot.

488
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:54,780
I-I was really acting a scene.

489
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:58,070
Dad, I don't want to eat mutton hot pot.

490
00:21:58,310 --> 00:22:00,530
I want you to go home with me.

491
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:02,120
Let's go!

492
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:03,650
What happened?

493
00:22:04,030 --> 00:22:04,760
Hongmei said

494
00:22:05,010 --> 00:22:05,660
she'd like to come

495
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:08,420
to Beijing to see what your life
has been like in these years.

496
00:22:08,420 --> 00:22:09,700
I told you before

497
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:12,010
that you couldn't
conceal the truth forever.

498
00:22:12,010 --> 00:22:13,500
Hongmei feels bad for you.

499
00:22:13,530 --> 00:22:15,900
-She cried multiple times in hometown.
-Fine, fine.

500
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:16,900
I don't blame you.

501
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:18,880
It's a good thing that they're here.

502
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,400
I can show them around in Beijing

503
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,260
and get Hongmei

504
00:22:21,350 --> 00:22:22,480
medical treatment.

505
00:22:22,830 --> 00:22:23,770
Xiaobao, come here!

506
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:24,420
Come!

507
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:25,500
Come on in now.

508
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:32,510
What do you think?

509
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:33,720
Let me take this.

510
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,030
Beijing is absolutely huge.

511
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:39,700
Of course.

512
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,030
Dad,

513
00:22:41,290 --> 00:22:42,610
is here where you live?

514
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:43,940
The place I live in

515
00:22:43,980 --> 00:22:45,530
is much bigger than this.

516
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:47,620
But it's too far away.

517
00:22:47,980 --> 00:22:49,040
So we'll stay here,

518
00:22:49,330 --> 00:22:50,930
inside the Second Ring Road.

519
00:22:58,980 --> 00:22:59,420
Hey,

520
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:00,670
Xiaobao.

521
00:23:01,770 --> 00:23:04,830
Tomorrow, we'll take your mother
to hospital first,

522
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,860
and then go to Tian'anmen Square.

523
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:07,540
Really?

524
00:23:07,740 --> 00:23:09,780
We'll take some nice photos.

525
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,320
Great.

526
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:13,380
When school starts,

527
00:23:13,530 --> 00:23:15,790
you can show your classmates the photos.

528
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:17,940
They'll find you admirable.

529
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:20,880
It smells so good.

530
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,010
None of your classmates

531
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:25,850
have been to Tian'anmen Square.

532
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:27,310
I can do it myself. I can.

533
00:23:27,310 --> 00:23:28,610
Let me... It's dirty.

534
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:29,920
It's too dirty.

535
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:31,080
Give it to me.

536
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:33,050
There it goes.

537
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:35,970
All good.

538
00:23:38,330 --> 00:23:41,310
I'll go... wash up.

539
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:44,880
I...

540
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:51,160
I'll give you a hug after I wash up.

541
00:23:54,290 --> 00:23:56,350
Dad, what were you two talking about?

542
00:23:57,050 --> 00:23:58,780
What could we be talking about?

543
00:23:59,050 --> 00:24:00,850
We were talking about
giving you a beating.

544
00:24:00,850 --> 00:24:02,180
Don't you think I understand what I saw?

545
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:03,710
What do you understand now?

546
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:05,270
Sit down.

547
00:24:05,420 --> 00:24:06,500
Get some rest.

548
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:55,410
Once it gets dark,

549
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:58,220
you can't read

550
00:24:59,090 --> 00:25:00,610
my lips

551
00:25:01,790 --> 00:25:04,220
or see my gestures.

552
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,340
I really wish

553
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,810
that someday, we could

554
00:25:10,850 --> 00:25:12,500
have a heart-to-heart talk

555
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,720
and whisper in each other's ear.

556
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:42,420
These days have been really rough for me.

557
00:25:43,130 --> 00:25:44,430
That surgery

558
00:25:45,420 --> 00:25:46,150
can cure you,

559
00:25:47,700 --> 00:25:49,030
but it's too expensive.

560
00:25:49,850 --> 00:25:51,380
I've been so anxious lately

561
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,570
that I've got ulcers all over my mouth.

562
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,590
My throat is inflamed too.

563
00:25:58,050 --> 00:25:59,250
I just hate myself...

564
00:26:07,220 --> 00:26:07,620
for...

565
00:26:08,590 --> 00:26:09,700
not being capable

566
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:12,210
and not having that much money.

567
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:15,200
If I could smash up my bones

568
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:16,900
and sell them,

569
00:26:18,030 --> 00:26:19,660
I would,

570
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:23,210
so as to get you a cochlear implant.

571
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:32,930
I want to... sing Yu Opera for you.

572
00:26:33,850 --> 00:26:34,980
When our son grows up

573
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:36,960
and gets married,

574
00:26:37,810 --> 00:26:40,470
I wish you could also say a few words
on the stage.

575
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:42,410
If you were able to speak,

576
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:44,660
you would definitely

577
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,970
be more articulate than me.

578
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,160
You're still up?

579
00:27:01,540 --> 00:27:03,990
Let's go to sleep.

580
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:05,970
I'll sleep.

581
00:27:08,390 --> 00:27:10,370
Yes, I will.

582
00:27:13,770 --> 00:27:15,160
Gentle pats...

583
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:17,930
for each other.

584
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:21,810
Who is it?

585
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,660
This is a room inspection.

586
00:27:23,830 --> 00:27:24,270
What?

587
00:27:27,140 --> 00:27:27,700
It's okay.

588
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:28,960
Nothing's happening.

589
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:31,720
It's fine.

590
00:27:36,570 --> 00:27:37,830
Police officers?

591
00:27:38,090 --> 00:27:39,350
Everyone in the room, come out

592
00:27:39,350 --> 00:27:40,590
for a routine inspection.

593
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:41,940
Do you have your ID cards with you?

594
00:27:41,940 --> 00:27:43,270
Take them out for registration.

595
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:43,940
Okay, sure.

596
00:27:43,980 --> 00:27:44,400
Got it.

597
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:52,310
Give it to me.

598
00:27:53,830 --> 00:27:54,950
Officer, our IDs.

599
00:28:03,530 --> 00:28:04,700
Who is this woman?

600
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,220
What's the relationship of you two?

601
00:28:06,220 --> 00:28:07,680
S-She is my wife.

602
00:28:08,070 --> 00:28:10,070
She brought our son here to visit me.

603
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:12,510
Please show me a marriage certificate.

604
00:28:12,510 --> 00:28:12,850
What?

605
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:14,770
S-She really is my wife.

606
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,260
Then just show us

607
00:28:16,290 --> 00:28:17,880
some marriage certificate.

608
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,830
Well, neither of us has brought

609
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:21,300
a marriage certificate.

610
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:23,050
Don't you have our IDs now?

611
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:25,190
W-We have been married

612
00:28:25,310 --> 00:28:26,440
for more than 10 years.

613
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:28,370
L-Look how big our son is.

614
00:28:28,660 --> 00:28:29,790
But how do you prove it?

615
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:30,660
Officer,

616
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:31,480
I can prove it.

617
00:28:31,530 --> 00:28:32,530
I'm their child.

618
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:36,430
Yes, he's our child.

619
00:28:40,340 --> 00:28:40,850
Well,

620
00:28:40,850 --> 00:28:42,180
she's speech impaired.

621
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:43,140
My mom is saying

622
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:45,130
that she's my dad's wife

623
00:28:45,270 --> 00:28:46,350
and that I'm her son.

624
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,680
There are rules in place.

625
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:48,640
For a man and a woman
to sleep in the same room,

626
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,090
they must provide a marriage certificate.

627
00:28:50,090 --> 00:28:51,810
Please understand
that we have our duties to fulfill.

628
00:28:51,810 --> 00:28:52,810
Now get yourselves ready

629
00:28:52,810 --> 00:28:53,790
and go with us.

630
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:54,490
Don't...

631
00:28:55,010 --> 00:28:56,390
Fine then...

632
00:28:56,460 --> 00:28:59,150
I will get dressed and leave

633
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:00,800
with you myself. Is it okay?

634
00:29:02,330 --> 00:29:03,210
It's...

635
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,520
It's okay. I...

636
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:10,410
My mom is saying

637
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:12,920
that she fell seriously ill
and suddenly went deaf

638
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,300
a few years ago.

639
00:29:14,770 --> 00:29:15,480
Gradually,

640
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:17,570
she also lost her ability to speak.

641
00:29:28,270 --> 00:29:29,330
But my dad has never

642
00:29:29,330 --> 00:29:30,510
resented her for that.

643
00:29:30,510 --> 00:29:31,550
He still takes good care

644
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:32,510
of me and her.

645
00:29:33,070 --> 00:29:33,750
My dad

646
00:29:33,810 --> 00:29:34,860
came to Beijing

647
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:36,620
to earn money exactly for her.

648
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:40,830
My mom is saying

649
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,920
that my dad only has her as his wife.

650
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:43,880
And she...

651
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:45,480
only has my dad as her family.

652
00:29:46,330 --> 00:29:47,160
Hey, Mom,

653
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:49,790
how could you forget about me?

654
00:29:49,810 --> 00:29:51,270
Aren't I also your family?

655
00:29:59,590 --> 00:30:00,640
My mom is saying

656
00:30:00,790 --> 00:30:01,850
that my dad has been

657
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:02,770
running

658
00:30:02,850 --> 00:30:04,900
back and forth between Beijing and home.

659
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,310
In order to have her cured,

660
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:08,510
my dad has been through much suffering.

661
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:10,170
In addition,

662
00:30:10,220 --> 00:30:12,000
it was not until today that she realized

663
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,760
that my dad had suffered

664
00:30:14,050 --> 00:30:14,900
tremendously

665
00:30:15,330 --> 00:30:16,590
for her and our family.

666
00:30:17,220 --> 00:30:18,140
She considers

667
00:30:18,270 --> 00:30:20,340
herself to be a lucky woman

668
00:30:20,570 --> 00:30:22,050
for meeting such a wonderful man

669
00:30:22,050 --> 00:30:22,950
like my dad.

670
00:30:27,380 --> 00:30:28,490
Officers,

671
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,200
my dad is a good person.

672
00:30:31,510 --> 00:30:33,630
I also just found out today

673
00:30:34,270 --> 00:30:36,470
that my dad,
for the sake of me and my mom,

674
00:30:36,530 --> 00:30:37,930
has done many exhausting

675
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:39,260
and dirty jobs.

676
00:30:42,940 --> 00:30:43,660
It's okay.

677
00:30:43,740 --> 00:30:45,050
Officer,

678
00:30:45,050 --> 00:30:47,700
can we have a word in private?

679
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:49,840
Please come with me.

680
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:54,910
In fact,

681
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:57,010
I'm a long-term tenant

682
00:30:57,110 --> 00:30:58,710
at the Seasons Change Hostel

683
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:00,800
in Luogu Hutong.

684
00:31:01,090 --> 00:31:03,840
Officer Tang is quite familiar with me.

685
00:31:04,090 --> 00:31:05,130
I have his number.

686
00:31:05,460 --> 00:31:07,530
Why don't you talk to him?

687
00:31:08,550 --> 00:31:10,200
Now that you and your family have said so,

688
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:11,570
we'll verify your story
back at the station.

689
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:11,980
Okay.

690
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,250
If there is a problem,

691
00:31:13,250 --> 00:31:14,250
we will come find you again.

692
00:31:14,250 --> 00:31:15,310
Okay, sure.

693
00:31:18,940 --> 00:31:20,000
Mr. Cui, Mr. Cui!

694
00:31:20,150 --> 00:31:20,550
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

695
00:31:21,010 --> 00:31:22,000
Congratulations!

696
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,090
The director told me

697
00:31:23,090 --> 00:31:23,590
that I could

698
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:24,880
start getting prepared now.

699
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:25,550
Does it mean...

700
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:27,100
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

701
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:26,980
I've landed the part?

702
00:31:27,140 --> 00:31:27,740
Of course.

703
00:31:27,980 --> 00:31:29,090
He also told me about it just now.

704
00:31:29,090 --> 00:31:29,660
Mr. Cui,

705
00:31:29,350 --> 00:31:33,590
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

706
00:31:30,030 --> 00:31:31,160
if it weren't for you,

707
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:32,590
I would've given up long ago.

708
00:31:32,590 --> 00:31:33,640
Thank you, Mr. Cui.

709
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:34,440
Why thank me?

710
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:36,570
You should thank that guy instead.

711
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:37,310
Who?

712
00:31:38,050 --> 00:31:40,420
What's the point of hiding the truth
from me?

713
00:31:40,420 --> 00:31:41,950
I'd better not ask too much.

714
00:31:43,010 --> 00:31:44,400
I have things to do later.

715
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,180
So I need to go now.

716
00:31:45,180 --> 00:31:46,480
I just stopped by to see you.

717
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,450
Listen,

718
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:49,400
this is a great role.

719
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,610
Do take it seriously.

720
00:31:50,610 --> 00:31:51,440
If you rises to fame for it,

721
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:53,010
you could be the female lead
in the next show, right?

722
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:54,380
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

723
00:31:54,270 --> 00:31:54,720
Bye!

724
00:32:12,490 --> 00:32:14,880
[Cashier]

725
00:32:16,410 --> 00:32:20,250
[Cashier]

726
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,730
What are you doing here?

727
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:43,300
Did you get me that part

728
00:32:43,510 --> 00:32:45,240
in the Golden Garden at Sunset?

729
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:49,150
It was no big deal.

730
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:50,720
Here's the story.

731
00:32:50,750 --> 00:32:52,000
I helped the filming crew

732
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,440
address some funding problems.

733
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:54,790
They always felt

734
00:32:54,810 --> 00:32:56,210
that they owed me a favor.

735
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:58,200
Then I mentioned in passing
that you could be

736
00:32:58,200 --> 00:32:58,960
a good fit.

737
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:03,580
Do you like the role?

738
00:33:04,160 --> 00:33:05,190
I want to play it.

739
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:07,850
But I don't want to owe you anything

740
00:33:07,850 --> 00:33:08,580
for this job.

741
00:33:13,380 --> 00:33:14,920
This is not a huge production.

742
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:16,320
The role is not that good.

743
00:33:16,350 --> 00:33:18,850
I was too embarrassed
to even bring it up to you.

744
00:33:18,850 --> 00:33:19,640
You're overthinking it.

745
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,170
Come on, let's talk inside.

746
00:33:37,010 --> 00:33:40,140
Maybe we don't have to get in there.

747
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,740
Let's catch up another day?

748
00:33:46,810 --> 00:33:48,700
Hey, why do you have to be so stubborn?

749
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:49,760
Why must you leave?

750
00:33:50,250 --> 00:33:51,720
Let's just fill out a form first.

751
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:54,140
Filling out a form won't cost a dime.

752
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:56,780
I'm saying it's free of charge!

753
00:33:56,980 --> 00:33:58,660
The medical fee
is tens of thousands of yuan.

754
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:02,790
How much suffering will you have to
go through to earn that much?

755
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,740
B-But

756
00:34:04,740 --> 00:34:07,180
didn't the doctor say

757
00:34:07,180 --> 00:34:10,340
that your ears could be fixed?

758
00:34:10,420 --> 00:34:12,230
Can't we just get in the line first?

759
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:13,380
We'll get in the line

760
00:34:13,510 --> 00:34:13,960
and wait

761
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:16,980
till we can afford the treatment, alright?

762
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:20,460
I don't want to hear anything.

763
00:34:20,820 --> 00:34:24,360
I don't want to hear anything!

764
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:27,179
I just want you to go home with me.

765
00:34:27,380 --> 00:34:28,460
What? Go home?

766
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,000
Why not stay in Beijing?

767
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:30,820
No way!

768
00:34:31,590 --> 00:34:32,520
You can't leave.

769
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:34,170
What are you doing?

770
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:35,840
What are you doing?

771
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,440
Can't you just listen to me?

772
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,800
Just listen to me, okay?

773
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:39,900
Listen to me!

774
00:34:40,110 --> 00:34:42,050
Can't you just listen to me?

775
00:34:42,150 --> 00:34:44,670
Listen to me! Listen to me!

776
00:34:46,610 --> 00:34:47,790
Xiaobao, come here.

777
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:48,500
Come.

778
00:34:49,150 --> 00:34:50,780
Tell your mom

779
00:34:51,460 --> 00:34:52,719
your opinion.

780
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,380
How should I put it,

781
00:34:57,670 --> 00:34:58,320
Dad?

782
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:02,300
I want Mom to get her hearing back.

783
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:06,670
And I also want to see you every day.

784
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:29,010
I...

785
00:35:38,630 --> 00:35:41,480
No, we all must stay here.

786
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:47,490
Why are you calling this place?

787
00:35:48,300 --> 00:35:49,830
Northeasterner said that?

788
00:35:50,300 --> 00:35:52,000
Okay. What's the job then?

789
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:55,530
It's a piece of cake.

790
00:35:56,440 --> 00:35:58,210
I'll head over now, alright?

791
00:35:59,670 --> 00:36:01,010
Okay. See you in a bit.

792
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:04,110
Miss, thank you.

793
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:17,960
Hey,

794
00:36:20,010 --> 00:36:24,340
I need to go to work now.

795
00:36:27,050 --> 00:36:30,190
The two of you get some rest here.

796
00:36:31,610 --> 00:36:35,480
We'll talk about

797
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,130
the medical treatment later.

798
00:36:38,510 --> 00:36:39,130
Okay?

799
00:36:45,530 --> 00:36:46,060
Xiaobao.

800
00:36:47,460 --> 00:36:48,720
I'll be out for a while.

801
00:36:49,210 --> 00:36:50,890
Take good care of your mom.

802
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:51,690
Got it.

803
00:36:54,070 --> 00:36:56,530
Tomorrow,
I'll take you to the Summer Palace

804
00:36:56,710 --> 00:36:58,550
so you can ride the bronze ox there.

805
00:36:58,550 --> 00:36:59,050
Okay.

806
00:37:05,030 --> 00:37:06,030
I'm leaving then.

807
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:11,920
Come back early.

808
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:12,570
Sure.

809
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,520
Off I go.

810
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,120
Sir, how is it going?

811
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:27,090
Almost done.

812
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:28,210
Okay.

813
00:37:28,530 --> 00:37:29,690
After you finish,

814
00:37:29,730 --> 00:37:30,940
please conduct a check

815
00:37:30,940 --> 00:37:31,860
on every corner.

816
00:37:31,860 --> 00:37:32,280
Okay.

817
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,400
When it's done, please stay a bit

818
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:35,360
for a meal here.

819
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:37,030
I'll cook you some noodles.

820
00:37:37,090 --> 00:37:37,460
Okay.

821
00:37:38,260 --> 00:37:39,790
Actually, no, I can't stay.

822
00:37:40,050 --> 00:37:41,630
My wife and son

823
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:42,690
are waiting for me.

824
00:37:44,070 --> 00:37:45,800
Can I have the noodles packed?

825
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:46,760
Sure.

826
00:37:47,010 --> 00:37:48,880
Then please pack a larger portion for me.

827
00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:49,300
Sure!

828
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:50,800
Y-You go on with your work.

829
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:51,940
I'll go get the food ready now.

830
00:37:51,940 --> 00:37:52,690
Okay, thanks.

831
00:37:52,690 --> 00:37:53,350
No problem!

832
00:37:56,300 --> 00:37:57,500
Why are you back here?

833
00:37:57,510 --> 00:37:59,440
D-Did you leave something behind?

834
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,150
Leave something behind? I...

835
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:02,450
I stay in Room 208.

836
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:04,260
They've checked out.

837
00:38:05,530 --> 00:38:07,500
T-They've checked out?

838
00:38:08,450 --> 00:38:10,280
[Seasons Change Hostel]

839
00:38:20,150 --> 00:38:20,980
Mrs. Jiang,

840
00:38:21,130 --> 00:38:22,530
you are so pretty.

841
00:38:22,610 --> 00:38:24,780
No wonder Mr. Guo misses you every day.

842
00:38:26,050 --> 00:38:27,030
Why isn't Zongbao back yet?

843
00:38:27,030 --> 00:38:29,290
I can't wait to taste this spread of food.

844
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,840
-Zongbao!
-You're back.

845
00:38:31,670 --> 00:38:32,400
Why didn't you

846
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:34,150
tell us your wife had come for a visit?

847
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:34,610
This...

848
00:38:36,650 --> 00:38:37,590
Take a seat now.

849
00:38:37,590 --> 00:38:38,710
What's all this gesturing about?

850
00:38:38,710 --> 00:38:39,880
Hurry, take a seat.

851
00:38:40,030 --> 00:38:41,430
Dig in. Start eating now.

852
00:38:41,890 --> 00:38:42,340
I need to wash up.

853
00:38:42,340 --> 00:38:43,780
-Don't go.
-Why wash up at all?

854
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:45,110
Just sit down and eat.

855
00:38:45,110 --> 00:38:45,610
Quick.

856
00:38:45,610 --> 00:38:47,170
Come on, let me take the bag.

857
00:39:01,230 --> 00:39:02,030
Mrs. Jiang...

858
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,530
Sit down, everyone.

859
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:05,970
Please sit down.

860
00:39:06,230 --> 00:39:07,460
Mrs. Jiang is asking us to sit.

861
00:39:07,460 --> 00:39:08,320
Be seated then.

862
00:39:14,630 --> 00:39:15,170
Don't drink that much.

863
00:39:15,170 --> 00:39:16,900
-Easy on the drink.
-Easy on it.

864
00:39:20,870 --> 00:39:24,980
[Endeavor]

865
00:39:35,170 --> 00:39:36,290
My mom is saying

866
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:38,070
that my dad was afraid that we'd see

867
00:39:38,070 --> 00:39:39,550
how hard his life is,

868
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:40,380
so he didn't bring us

869
00:39:40,380 --> 00:39:41,500
to Beijing.

870
00:39:43,110 --> 00:39:44,170
But now as she's here,

871
00:39:44,170 --> 00:39:46,230
she can actually put her mind at ease.

872
00:39:48,130 --> 00:39:49,210
My mom would like to

873
00:39:49,260 --> 00:39:50,730
thank you all today.

874
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,820
She's saying that she's grateful to you

875
00:39:55,820 --> 00:39:57,820
for taking care of my dad for so long.

876
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:02,700
My mom is saying

877
00:40:02,820 --> 00:40:04,750
that she really loves this hostel.

878
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:08,220
She didn't realize

879
00:40:08,260 --> 00:40:09,320
how happily my dad lives here

880
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,950
until she came for a look.

881
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,340
All of you are good people.

882
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:28,840
A toast to Mrs. Jiang.

883
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:29,320
Come on.

884
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:34,360
Xiaobao, what's the gesture
of "thank you"?

885
00:40:35,610 --> 00:40:36,410
Mrs. Jiang...

886
00:40:50,950 --> 00:40:51,500
Drink up!

887
00:40:59,110 --> 00:41:00,500
Sit down. Sit.

888
00:41:00,710 --> 00:41:01,770
Dig in.

889
00:41:02,550 --> 00:41:05,130
My wife is a wonderful cook.

890
00:41:05,170 --> 00:41:05,690
Eat the food

891
00:41:05,690 --> 00:41:06,820
before it gets cold.

892
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:07,440
What a delicious spread

893
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,880
Mrs. Jiang prepared for us.

894
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:09,320
Right?

895
00:41:09,340 --> 00:41:11,280
You should've brought

896
00:41:11,460 --> 00:41:12,780
your fantastic wife and son to Beijing

897
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:13,760
for a gathering with us.

898
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:14,610
Yeah.

899
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:15,900
Here, Son.

900
00:41:17,300 --> 00:41:20,260
Mrs. Jiang, Mr. Guo missed you dearly.

901
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:26,950
That's right.

902
00:41:27,260 --> 00:41:28,730
Whenever Zongbao talks about you,

903
00:41:28,730 --> 00:41:29,940
he beams with joy

904
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,220
and has a lot to say.

905
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:35,530
W-When have I ever talked about her?

906
00:41:35,530 --> 00:41:36,540
How have you not?

907
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:38,070
Every night when you talk

908
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:38,670
in your sleep,

909
00:41:38,670 --> 00:41:40,830
you call Mrs. Jiang's name.

910
00:41:41,010 --> 00:41:41,960
I don't. Do I?

911
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:42,910
You can ask them.

912
00:41:43,010 --> 00:41:44,270
I-I've heard it too.

913
00:41:45,230 --> 00:41:46,090
You're no good.

914
00:41:51,130 --> 00:41:51,530
What?

915
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:55,360
It's dirt.

916
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,490
So tasty.

917
00:41:57,300 --> 00:41:59,760
Dad, I'd like to make a toast
to everyone too.

918
00:41:59,840 --> 00:42:00,670
Go ahead then.

919
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:01,980
Guys, listen,

920
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:05,290
Xiaobao has a few words to say.

921
00:42:05,550 --> 00:42:06,780
He'd like to make toast

922
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:08,320
to all of you, just like I did.

923
00:42:08,320 --> 00:42:09,400
A warm welcome for him!

924
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:11,060
Say a few words then, Xiaobao!

925
00:42:11,650 --> 00:42:13,310
-Come on.
-The floor's yours.

926
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:15,220
Ladies and gentlemen,

927
00:42:15,630 --> 00:42:16,630
over these years,

928
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,100
my dad has kept telling me

929
00:42:19,340 --> 00:42:22,100
to come to Beijing when I grow up.

930
00:42:19,410 --> 00:42:26,990
[Endeavor]

931
00:42:22,550 --> 00:42:23,860
But I never knew

932
00:42:24,230 --> 00:42:26,700
why I should come to Beijing.

933
00:42:27,380 --> 00:42:29,940
Just now, I realized the reason.

934
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:32,720
What did you figure out?

935
00:42:33,420 --> 00:42:35,620
It turns out that my dad lives

936
00:42:35,840 --> 00:42:38,080
with a singer, a musician,

937
00:42:38,340 --> 00:42:39,360
a big star,

938
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:42,070
a great screenwriter who writes for films

939
00:42:42,070 --> 00:42:43,470
and a brilliant painter.

940
00:42:44,300 --> 00:42:45,790
I've never seen these many

941
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:49,170
prominent figures
in the county or village.

942
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:52,120
Dad, now I understand

943
00:42:52,670 --> 00:42:54,690
how splendid Beijing is.
